The article discusses the Republican-led Senate's passing of a tax reform bill that aims to lower taxes for families and small businesses. The bill includes provisions such as lower, simpler, and fairer tax rates for middle-class families, doubling the child tax credit, preserving the adoption tax credit, and roughly doubling the standard deduction. The article also mentions that the bill has the support of the National Federation of Independent Business and highlights the repeal of ObamaCare's individual mandate tax as another relief for low- and middle-income Americans. The article concludes by stating that lowering taxes is a central part of President Trump's agenda and that the Senate will work with the House to send a final tax reform bill to the President for his signature.